Description: Rim and body sherd (three joined fragments) of North Ionian pottery rosette bowl; pale brown clay with some silver mica; glaze fired orange; interior glazed; exterior: band at lip; two dot-tosettes preserved in frieze; three bands below; inscribed on exterior.
Curator's comments: Two of the sherds were re-registered in error as 1924,1201.210 and 211.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 292)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 668, no. 253)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.853)
